Package: accessibletablesR
Type: Package
Title: Creating accessible tables in an Excel workbook
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Matthew", "Minifie", email = "minifiemj@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Creates Excel spreadsheets which align as closely as possible to UK 
    Government Statistical Service's accessibility criteria. Relies upon the R 
    package 'openxlsx'. The package was developed using R 4.1.3, 'dplyr' 
    version 1.1.2, 'openxlsx' version 4.2.5.2, 'devtools' version 2.4.5, 'conflicted'
    version 1.2.0, 'stringr' version 1.5.0, 'purrr' version 1.0.1, 'rlang' version 1.1.0 and 
    'odsconvertr' version 0.2.2. Alternative options include the R package 'a11ytables' and the 
    Python package 'gptables'.
URL: https://github.com/minifiemj/accessibletablesR,
    https://minifiemj.github.io/accessibletablesR/
BugReports: https://github.com/minifiemj/accessibletablesR/issues
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.2.3
Depends:
    R (>= 3.3.0)
Imports:
    conflicted (>= 1.2.0),
    devtools (>= 2.4.5),
    dplyr (>= 1.1.2),
    odsconvertr,
    openxlsx (>= 4.2.5.2),
    purrr (>= 1.0.1),
    rlang (>= 1.1.0),
    stringr (>= 1.5.0)
Remotes:
